##A "beautiful" Hubei man: I am suspected of a new crown in the United States, but this is not the most terrible | sandwich

WECHAT china30s

Feature description, a platform that encourages you to write about your life. Founded in March 2011, it has a sandwich writing school and a media platform, China Sandwich, at the same time, we are committed to applying the story to cross-border product design, urban culture excavation, exhibition fair, space creation and other three-dimensional field.

It's written. It's written

It's been a sunny couple of days in the bay area. Across the Pacific, Wuhan, on the Yangtze Coast, is still wet and cold these days, with a 50% chance of rain forecast for today and tomorrow.

"We returned to the bay area from Hubei on January 14, which is more than three weeks ago, " said big J, a software engineer at a high-tech company in the bay area known as the senior "code farmer. ". His voice was calm, as if he had few emotional ups and downs, and he was unhurried in recalling an experience that his family would never forget.

Like many beautiful families, big J's family is in the country. Dual-earner families save a big vacation every year to travel back to China or on a long trip. This year, they returned home before the Christmas holiday. After a few days in their hometown of Hubei, they went to Yunnan with their wives. The mountains, rivers, lakes and seas of the motherland can not see all, as long as time to return home, we should seize the opportunity to go out and see more. During a week in Yunnan, big J received a message from a friend saying there was "pneumonia of unknown origin" in the city, but "it was just a notification, nothing special. " On January 4, when the family returned to Jingzhou, everything was peaceful and peaceful.

Take advantage of this great time, big J next few days and a few cities alone shuttle, friends, sightseeing. As a "hard core" skiing enthusiasts, big j this trip also made a special trip to Japan skiing. For the persistence of skiing, big J belongs to "see the danger of skiing, still love" . It wasn't until the 13th that I returned to Wuhan, where I spent the night. On the 14th, I boarded a flight back to the United States with my wife and two-year-old daughter.

Everything was going very well and it was a near-perfect holiday.

By the fourth day of his return, the change was overwhelming.

On Monday the 20th, big j began feeling sick in his throat after the CDC issued a new coronavirus warning on the 17th by Friday, usually my throat is sick, I don't know what it is, I feel it must be some kind of virus. On the 21st, Tuesday, "we saw on the news that the guy in Seattle had a seizure. " Big J started getting cold and fever.

"I started calling urgent care in my city, Tuesday, and I said I had just come back from Wuhan with cold symptoms and a fever, possibly with a coronavirus infection. Can you test there? "

"What is Coronavirus? Never heard of it, " said the hospital, feeling dazed over the phone. "They probably didn't know What it was yet, said it was undetectable, and told me to call my family doctor

The family doctor is to see a non-urgent minor illness, usually need to make an appointment some time in advance, big j called, also did not make an appointment with his family doctor, can only see a family doctor in the city of San Francisco. "They were pretty nervous before they went. They told me I'd get your mask when you got there, and they'd take you straight to the operating room instead of to the front desk. " Instead, "he just listened to my lungs. He said you didn't have the symptoms. " Big J demanded, "then you test me, to see what is the virus, ordinary flu virus or something else? " The doctor refused the request, said not to check, unlike.

Dispensary, sold out of face masks

"after looking at the first new crown case in Seattle, and based on the speculation from the market, it is very likely that my family and I were on the same flight as the guy, because Wuhan does not have a direct flight to Seattle. "

The fear of uncertainty began to build, but big J was still struggling to find an institution to give him a definitive answer.

Out of a responsible attitude to others, big J informed the unit of their own symptoms, coincidentally, another colleague also appeared uncomfortable, went to another hospital for examination. "I ended up getting tested because the hospital where my colleague went notified the San Francisco Department of Public Health. " Big J also tried to call the CDC several times, "They were very hard to get on the phone, and I finally got in touch. An operator read me a long introduction about the new coronavirus and told us that the disease is very contagious. BE CAREFUL! " Big J asked whether there is a place to do testing? "their advice was to isolate myself, they had no place to test me and leave me at home. "

Big J's biggest headache is just beginning.

Some people on wechat began to hear from the urge, want to know what the big J is. Because in the big J family back in the first week, before the flu symptoms, and friends and friends' children to meet a few meals, "with the increase in the number of cases on the news, everyone began to worry. "

Another bomb was also detonated. The Department of big J's company sent a short email to employees saying that a colleague had just returned from Wuhan with suspected cases and mentioned flu symptoms, but did not say that the colleague had isolated himself for several days, nor did it say that it had been tested for influenza a, nor did it say that new coronavirus testing was ongoing. The news spread like wildfire, and the wechat group inside various companies exploded. The contents of the ambiguous message were speculated to have mutated faster than a virus in people's transmission, "within an hour, we were in different wechat groups, and we saw different screenshots of messages, and someone started asking me if the person on Wechat was your husband, " big j's wife added nearby.

"This is ridiculous. No one can tell me where to do this test. I wanted to know what I had, and I wanted to tell my friends as soon as I could, but I had no idea the procedure was so unclear and complicated.

Anxious, continue to be isolated at home, but there is a two-year-old children, the big J couple's heart of worry gradually fermenting inflation, slowly turned into fear and helplessness. "A lot of times, I go upstairs with my food and when I'm done, I don't know where to do the dishes. Do you want me to wipe the DOORKNOB? Come downstairs in your shoes. You want me to clean your shoes? I've been wearing these gloves for days, and I'm afraid to touch anything in the house. The child looked at me and said, "Daddy, I dare not hold her either. "

Offline anxiety continues to fester online. Big J recalls: "A lot of things about human nature are magnified in this kind of crisis. From my experience, I saw People Gossiping, talking about the Virus Day in and day out, spreading all kinds of news. A lot of people couldn't stand it, so they had to retreat quietly. There were a lot of rumors, a lot of screenshots, a lot of typing and not typing, and it was really a few minutes later I saw my screenshots from different sources."

A virus, a Human Pandora. When we jump out of our Wechat Group, the painting style is not much different. Countless news stories chronicled the power of the disaster's shockwave. It can even be said that every Chinese family has been affected, but to varying degrees: Because of a retweeted request for better living, bi Yanwen, a Hubei girl who was forced to stay in a hotel in Shanghai, committed suicide after being "forced" by a netizen. The city of Wuhan is closed, and the lives and livelihoods of many people with chronic diseases are also under threat: AIDS patients who must be strictly medicated, those who can not get medicine, and expectant mothers who are at high risk of pregnancy, they are losing specialist medication and specialist guidance from Gynaecologists, and are dying without beds or resources for kidney dialysis patients. Countless heart-breaking stories tell of ordinary people's anxiety.

Finally, big J got a notice that a hospital in a nearby county could take samples in a negative pressure ward. There have been several cases in the bay area suspected of being harvested there. Big J's on his way. When a sample was taken on Thursday, big j daily urged the laboratory to inform the result, "helpless, very helpless. " To This Day, big J has not responded to Wechat, which many friends have asked, "really not in that state, not in the mood to reply. "

Finally, on the second Tuesday, big J received the result: Negative.

Negative pressure ward

To be examined

For a moment as if Manna fell, attached to the mid-air dust, finally attached to the dew brought on the wet, fell back to the ground.

As of early February, the CDC had tested 210 suspected samples and confirmed 12 cases. America's health care and emergency care systems are relatively sound, but pain can not be replaced or quantified, and we can only imagine the total darkness experienced by more than 200 families.

In this case, big J's wife experienced multiple information overload and emotional challenges. While her husband was in isolation, she took time off from work to take care of the baby, "public opinion is under a lot of pressure and doesn't have the time and energy to worry about your health. Big J's wife works for Gilead, the pharmaceutical company behind the new viral "wonder drug, " which has gone viral, when you see the CEO of your company, Patients First, saying, "there's hope, but it's also the right thing to do as a businessman. "

Crisis and opportunity are often printed on two sides of the same card. After Gilead successfully developed a cure for Hepatitis C a few years ago, it suffered a stock market crash, simply because the disease was cured and no one needed it anymore. At the same time, high-priced drugs are also subject to social stigma. "people actually like the icing on the cake, rather than the icing on the cake, " big J's wife continued, "For example, when a doctor sees you, we take it for granted, because it's their job, and we don't care if they're doing it with their lives; when a drug company develops a drug, it costs a lot of money, but a lot of people may feel that if you have this drug, you should give it to us at a lower price, or else it's unethical. " Because the stock market in Gilead has been flat for years, the crisis has accelerated the progress of Remdesivir's Phase III trials at home, and perhaps this time Gilead can turn the tables.

Big J's family left Hubei Province before the outbreak in China. The local public security bureau may lock the number of Hubei Province based on the roaming signal of the mobile phone, "Now my parents still receive regular phone calls from the Public Security Bureau asking them to report their body temperature, every day. " Big J's wife's family is still in Jingzhou, and her father and mother are separated from each other in two homes in the city, because "dad goes to work every day, contact people complex, he does not want to pass the risk to my mother. " Big J wife tone filled with worry and frustration. "My old father, has not come home yet, has been burning the midnight oil several times in a row. " Big J wife sends a weeping facial expression. Parents of the children of the "travel secret, afraid of late" anxiety, was overturned today, the children outside the city watching the city of the father and mother, care and love into tears, silent fall.

The most at risk is probably the cousin of big J's wife, a nurse at Wuhan Children's Hospital who has started collecting nucleic acid samples on the front line, after she was breast feeding. After the city was shut down, public transport was cut off and my cousin rode a shared bicycle to work. Recently, my cousin checked into a hotel next to the hospital and "stopped going home" to reduce the risk of infecting her family. His wife sent screenshots of the family, who said they were "great and brave. ".

On February 5th a lovely newborn baby, piperidone, fell to the ground, and 30 hours later the baby was diagnosed with new crown pneumonia, the first case of suspected mother to child transmission. The hospital where the baby was born is the children's hospital where big J's wife's cousin works.

Toward the end of our conversation, big J's wife drew a slow breath and summed up the experience in four words: grief and anger. In the previous phase of self-isolation, the slanders of gossip gave her a glimpse of "the harm done to the people of Hubei outside Hubei. I feel for them, I feel for them, what our little family has gone through is really nothing compared to these people, they have been hurt 1,000,10,000 times more than we have, after the isolation, the pain did not completely disappear, "I realized I needed to protect my family while maintaining my internal order and sense of justice. I was overly optimistic, and now I realize I can't do that. "

This disaster is not only the subversion of people's normal life, many people are no longer the former self, many things can not simply go back to the past.

An operator read me a long introduction about the new coronavirus and told us that the disease is very contagious. BE CAREFUL! " Big J asked whether there is a place to do testing? "their advice was to isolate myself, they had no place to test me and leave me at home. "

Big J's biggest headache is just beginning.

Some people on wechat began to hear from the urge, want to know what the big J is. Because in the big J family back in the first week, before the flu symptoms, and friends and friends' children to meet a few meals, "with the increase in the number of cases on the news, everyone began to worry. "

Another bomb was also detonated. The Department of big J's company sent a short email to employees saying that a colleague had just returned from Wuhan with suspected cases and mentioned flu symptoms, but did not say that the colleague had isolated himself for several days, nor did it say that it had been tested for influenza a, nor did it say that new coronavirus testing was ongoing. The news spread like wildfire, and the wechat group inside various companies exploded. The contents of the ambiguous message were speculated to have mutated faster than a virus in people's transmission, "within an hour, we were in different wechat groups, and we saw different screenshots of messages, and someone started asking me if the person on Wechat was your husband, " big j's wife added nearby.

"This is ridiculous. No one can tell me where to do this test. I wanted to know what I had, and I wanted to tell my friends as soon as I could, but I had no idea the procedure was so unclear and complicated.

Anxious, continue to be isolated at home, but there is a two-year-old children, the big J couple's heart of worry gradually fermenting inflation, slowly turned into fear and helplessness. "A lot of times, I go upstairs with my food and when I'm done, I don't know where to do the dishes. Do you want me to wipe the DOORKNOB? Come downstairs in your shoes. You want me to clean your shoes? I've been wearing these gloves for days, and I'm afraid to touch anything in the house. The child looked at me and said, "Daddy, I dare not hold her either. "

Offline anxiety continues to fester online. Big J recalls: "A lot of things about human nature are magnified in this kind of crisis. From my experience, I saw People Gossiping, talking about the Virus Day in and day out, spreading all kinds of news. A lot of people couldn't stand it, so they had to retreat quietly. There were a lot of rumors, a lot of screenshots, a lot of typing and not typing, and it was really a few minutes later I saw my screenshots from different sources."

A virus, a Human Pandora. When we jump out of our Wechat Group, the painting style is not much different. Countless news stories chronicled the power of the disaster's shockwave. It can even be said that every Chinese family has been affected, but to varying degrees: Because of a retweeted request for better living, bi Yanwen, a Hubei girl who was forced to stay in a hotel in Shanghai, committed suicide after being "forced" by a netizen. The city of Wuhan is closed, and the lives and livelihoods of many people with chronic diseases are also under threat: AIDS patients who must be strictly medicated, those who can not get medicine, and expectant mothers who are at high risk of pregnancy, they are losing specialist medication and specialist guidance from Gynaecologists, and are dying without beds or resources for kidney dialysis patients. Countless heart-breaking stories tell of ordinary people's anxiety.

Finally, big J got a notice that a hospital in a nearby county could take samples in a negative pressure ward. There have been several cases in the bay area suspected of being harvested there. Big J's on his way. When a sample was taken on Thursday, big j daily urged the laboratory to inform the result, "helpless, very helpless. " To This Day, big J has not responded to Wechat, which many friends have asked, "really not in that state, not in the mood to reply. "

Finally, on the second Tuesday, big J received the result: Negative.

"after looking at the first new crown case in Seattle, and based on the speculation from the market, it is very likely that my family and I were on the same flight as the guy, because Wuhan does not have a direct flight to Seattle. "

The fear of uncertainty began to build, but big J was still struggling to find an institution to give him a definitive answer.

Out of a responsible attitude to others, big J informed the unit of their own symptoms, coincidentally, another colleague also appeared uncomfortable, went to another hospital for examination. "I ended up getting tested because the hospital where my colleague went notified the San Francisco Department of Public Health. " Big J also tried to call the CDC several times, "They were very hard to get on the phone, and I finally got in touch. For a moment as if Manna fell, attached to the mid-air dust, finally attached to the dew brought on the wet, fell back to the ground.

As of early February, the CDC had tested 210 suspected samples and confirmed 12 cases. America's health care and emergency care systems are relatively sound, but pain can not be replaced or quantified, and we can only imagine the total darkness experienced by more than 200 families.

In this case, big J's wife experienced multiple information overload and emotional challenges. While her husband was in isolation, she took time off from work to take care of the baby, "public opinion is under a lot of pressure and doesn't have the time and energy to worry about your health. Big J's wife works for Gilead, the pharmaceutical company behind the new viral "wonder drug, " which has gone viral, when you see the CEO of your company, Patients First, saying, "there's hope, but it's also the right thing to do as a businessman. "

Crisis and opportunity are often printed on two sides of the same card. After Gilead successfully developed a cure for Hepatitis C a few years ago, it suffered a stock market crash, simply because the disease was cured and no one needed it anymore. At the same time, high-priced drugs are also subject to social stigma. "people actually like the icing on the cake, rather than the icing on the cake, " big J's wife continued, "For example, when a doctor sees you, we take it for granted, because it's their job, and we don't care if they're doing it with their lives; when a drug company develops a drug, it costs a lot of money, but a lot of people may feel that if you have this drug, you should give it to us at a lower price, or else it's unethical. " Because the stock market in Gilead has been flat for years, the crisis has accelerated the progress of Remdesivir's Phase III trials at home, and perhaps this time Gilead can turn the tables.

Big J's family left Hubei Province before the outbreak in China. The local public security bureau may lock the number of Hubei Province based on the roaming signal of the mobile phone, "Now my parents still receive regular phone calls from the Public Security Bureau asking them to report their body temperature, every day. " Big J's wife's family is still in Jingzhou, and her father and mother are separated from each other in two homes in the city, because "dad goes to work every day, contact people complex, he does not want to pass the risk to my mother. " Big J wife tone filled with worry and frustration. "My old father, has not come home yet, has been burning the midnight oil several times in a row. " Big J wife sends a weeping facial expression. Parents of the children of the "travel secret, afraid of late" anxiety, was overturned today, the children outside the city watching the city of the father and mother, care and love into tears, silent fall.

The most at risk is probably the cousin of big J's wife, a nurse at Wuhan Children's Hospital who has started collecting nucleic acid samples on the front line, after she was breast feeding. After the city was shut down, public transport was cut off and my cousin rode a shared bicycle to work. Recently, my cousin checked into a hotel next to the hospital and "stopped going home" to reduce the risk of infecting her family. His wife sent screenshots of the family, who said they were "great and brave. ".

On February 5th a lovely newborn baby, piperidone, fell to the ground, and 30 hours later the baby was diagnosed with new crown pneumonia, the first case of suspected mother to child transmission. The hospital where the baby was born is the children's hospital where big J's wife's cousin works.

Toward the end of our conversation, big J's wife drew a slow breath and summed up the experience in four words: grief and anger. In the previous phase of self-isolation, the slanders of gossip gave her a glimpse of "the harm done to the people of Hubei outside Hubei. I feel for them, I feel for them, what our little family has gone through is really nothing compared to these people, they have been hurt 1,000,10,000 times more than we have, after the isolation, the pain did not completely disappear, "I realized I needed to protect my family while maintaining my internal order and sense of justice. I was overly optimistic, and now I realize I can't do that. "

This disaster is not only the subversion of people's normal life, many people are no longer the former self, many things can not simply go back to the past.
